The paper discusses a framework for learning decision-making strategies through observation, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The framework also involves personalized embeddings, which are commonly used in machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also mentions a user study to assess the interpretability of the decision-making models, which falls under the category of human-computer interaction (cs.HC). The framework is applied to a real-world planning domain, which falls under the category of robotics (cs.RO) and systems and control (cs.SY).
